# Normalize line endings. Source files are checked out as LF on every platform
# so JVM source-position macros (e.g. Kyo's `Frame` / kyo-test `assert`) don't
# miscount offsets on CRLF and crash with StringIndexOutOfBoundsException.
# Without this, GitHub's Windows runners (core.autocrlf=true) check out CRLF and
# the test compile fails. See getkyo/kyo#1678 thread / Eleven19/kymora#3.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Windows batch launcher must keep CRLF.
*.bat text eol=crlf
*.cmd text eol=crlf
